						               													<description>Kradia: Wild Hunt Festival (&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#175;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#171;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#137;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#143;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#149;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#167;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#185;) is a JRPG-turned-board game set in the colorful world of Kradia. In the game, up to four players are tasked with forming a party of adventurers and combining their powers to defeat a series of bosses. As a cooperative fantasy-themed boss-battle game, players must synergize their abilities and employ effective combat strategies&amp;mdash;via the utilization of items and their characters' unique class abilities&amp;mdash;to defeat a collection of bosses.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each character in Wild Hunt Festival has an assigned role (or class) such as attacker, healer, defender, etc. These characters possess their own combat statistics, strengths &amp;amp; weaknesses, and class-specific skills that all must be leveraged throughout each battle and in conjunction with one another to overcome the game's challenging monsters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are two modes of play in Wild Hunt Festival. Story Mode, which is the game's primary play mode, offers a campaign-like progression system where players start at level 1 and take on a series of bosses, leveling between each fight. In Challenge Mode, players start at the level 4 (max level) and fight a single super-charged boss.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;publisher's summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
